# TODO Format

## 1. Standard TODO Format

Use the following format for TODO comments:

```
// TODO(github_id): description [issue reference]
```

### Format Components
- `github_id`: Your GitHub username (required)
- `description`: Brief description of what needs to be done (required)
- `[issue reference]`: Optional reference to issue, PR, or other context

### Examples

```cpp
// TODO(houchen_li): Implement error handling for edge cases
// TODO(houchen_li): Optimize this algorithm for large datasets [#123]
// TODO(houchen_li): Add unit tests for this function [issue: BOYLE-456]
// TODO(houchen_li): Refactor after API stabilizes [PR #789]
```

## 2. Rules
- **REQUIRED**: Always include your GitHub ID in parentheses
- Keep descriptions concise but informative
- Use `[issue reference]` to link to related issues, PRs, or tickets when applicable
- TODO comments should describe actionable tasks
- Remove TODO comments once the task is completed
